<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB00085</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT REQUIRING ALL GOVERNMENT AND NON-GOVERNMENT OFFICES AND ESTABLISHMENTS TO ADOPT POLICIES TO PREVENT AND ADDRESS THE ACTS OF BULLYING AND OTHER SIMILAR ACTS IN THEIR WORKPLACE</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SHORT TITLE : Requiring All Government And Non-government Offices And Establishments To Adopt Policies To Prevent And Address The Acts Of Bullying And Other Similar Acts In Their Workplace</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Seeks to mandate and compel all government and non-government offices and establishments to adopt policies to prevent and address office bullying and other similar acts in their respective institutions.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ALIAS NAME : “Anti-Office Bullying Act of 2016”</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>GARBIN, ALFREDO JR. A., CO, ELIZALDY S.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2019-07-01</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Olivarez (000 2019-09-04)</td><td>2. Sy-Alvarado (000 2019-10-17)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON CIVIL SERVICE AND PROFESSIONAL REGULATION ON 2019-07-23</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SECONDARILY REFERRED TO THE COMMITTEE(S) ON LABOR AND EMPLOYMENT</td></tr></table>